The paper deals with the construction of aperiodic tile sets, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of fixed-point (self-referential) argument also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper presents a new construction method, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of computational complexity (cs.CC).
